  <h3>Design goals</h3>
  <ul> 
    <li><b>Fully programmable</b> - multi-layer keymaps, mouse keys, oneshot modifiers, macros, ...</li>
    <li><b>Full split with laptop wide separation</b> - most comfortable hand positioning I've found</li>
    <li><b>Non-staggered columns</b> - human fingers don't move diagonally</li>
    <li><b>Staggered rows</b> - human fingers have different lengths</li>
    <li><b>Just enough keys you can reach</b> - no stretching, no hand movement</li>
    <li><b>Multiple thumb keys</b> - pity to waste two thumbs on just one key</li>
    <li><b>Trackpoint on home-row</b> - great mouse at your finger tip (<a href="https://github.com/alonswartz/trackpoint">guide</a>)</li>
    <li><b>Tactile mechanical switches</b> - once you go mechanical, you can't go back</li>
    <li><b>Full hand with integrated wrist rests</b> - mobility and tenting</li>
    <li><b>Small, minimal and compact</b> - mobility</li>
  </ul>

